## Documentation Usage Guidelines

### When providing code suggestions or answers:
1. Always reference the relevant documentation URL when applicable
2. Check Pipecat documentation before suggesting implementation patterns
3. Refer to official CLI reference for command-line operations
4. Use Docker starter template as baseline for containerization
5. Reference error codes documentation when handling exceptions
6. Consult scaling documentation for performance considerations

### Documentation Priority Order:
1. Official Pipecat documentation (docs.pipecat.daily.co)
2. Pipecat AI guides (docs.pipecat.ai)
3. GitHub repository examples
4. Docker official templates

### Code References:
- Before suggesting any Pipecat-related code, check the relevant documentation section
- Include documentation links in code comments when implementing features
- Reference CLI documentation for deployment and management scripts
- Use official Docker template as starting point for containerization

## Documentation Update Protocol
- Verify documentation links are current before providing suggestions
- When documentation is unclear, reference multiple sources
- Prefer official documentation over third-party resources
- Include version-specific documentation when relevant

